L. BUCKI & SON LUMBER CO. v. ATLANTIC LUMBER CO. et al. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. April 7, 1903.) No. 1,143. Appeal from the Circuit Court of the United States for the Northern District of Florida.

Before PARDEE, McCORMICK, and SHELBY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

We find nothing in the reasons presented for a rehearing to make us doubt the correctness of the decision heretofore rendered (121 Fed. 233), and the rehearings applied for are denied.
